HEADWORD: Pluviometer
<hw>Plu`vi*om"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>pluvia</ets> rain + <ets>-meter</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>pluviom⟦egrave⟧tre</ets>.]</ety> <def>An instrument for
ascertaining the amount of rainfall at any place in a given time; a rain
gauge.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pluviometrical</ent>⟦br⟧
